{#- docs/PRODUCT.md — full projection of .specify/ggen-product.ttl, ggen's
    product-mirror ontology. Every table row is a real fact asserted in the
    ontology (verb, pipeline stage, or FM-* diagnostic code), each carrying a
    real file:line citation checked by
    crates/ggen-engine/tests/product_mirror_conformance.rs. -#}
{%- set verbs = sparql(query='PREFIX prod: <http://ggen.org/product#> SELECT ?noun ?verb ?citation WHERE { ?x a prod:CliVerb ; prod:noun ?noun ; prod:verb ?verb ; prod:citation ?citation . } ORDER BY ?noun ?verb') -%}
{%- set stages = sparql(query='PREFIX prod: <http://ggen.org/product#> SELECT ?span ?citation WHERE { ?x a prod:PipelineStage ; prod:spanName ?span ; prod:citation ?citation . } ORDER BY ?span') -%}
{%- set codes = sparql(query='PREFIX prod: <http://ggen.org/product#> SELECT ?family ?number ?citation WHERE { ?x a prod:DiagnosticCode ; prod:family ?family ; prod:number ?number ; prod:citation ?citation . } ORDER BY ?family ?number') -%}
# ggen Product Surface

GENERATED by `ggen sync` from `.specify/ggen-product.ttl` — edit the ontology, not this file.

Conformance between this ontology and the real source is enforced by
`crates/ggen-engine/tests/product_mirror_conformance.rs` (`cargo test -p ggen-engine --test
product_mirror_conformance`): every fact below has a real `file:line` citation, and that test
re-scans the cited source at test time to assert two-way equality.

